"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e4b355",
"children":[
"First-line treatment includes pericardiocentesis or surgical drainage plus IV normal saline for hemodynamically unstable patients."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s18_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"4c8eac",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 44-year-old woman with a history of ovarian cancer presents with fatigue, dyspnea, and peripheral edema. Examination shows ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"jugular venous distention",
"children":[
"JVD"
]
},
" that increases with inspiration, reduced heart sounds, ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"blood pressure",
"children":[
"BP"
]
},
" of 94/50 mm Hg, and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"hazard ratio; heart rate",
"children":[
"HR"
]
},
" of 132/min. A 20 mm Hg pulsus paradoxus is present."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"5bb8e2",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose acute pericardial tamponade, probably secondary to metastatic disease. For management, select pericardiocentesis."
]
}
]
}
]
},
